<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>RADIATOR, REMOVE AND REPLACE - 7300, 7400, 7500, 7600, 7700 Models - RADIATOR AND COMPONENT REMOVAL - CHARGE
        AIR COOLER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="5">
        <title>CHARGE AIR COOLER</title>
        <para>After removal (if equipped) of the external transmission cooler, the charge air cooler assembly must be
            removed. If the chassis is equipped with an internal transmission cooler refer to (
            <hotlnk document="s12010_5.xml" xrefid="f1201025">Figure 25 Item 1,</hotlnk>
            and
            <hotlnk document="s12010_5.xml" xrefid="f1201026">Figure 26, Item 5</hotlnk>) and follow disconnect
            procedures.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate and remove the charge air cooler mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201016">Figure 16, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201016" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201016.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 16. Charge Air Cooler Mounting Bolt Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER MOUNTING BOLT AND BUSHING (PASSENGER SIDE SHOWN)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate upper radiator frame and recirculation shield assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201017">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201017" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201017.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                         scalefitheight="272px"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Top Recirculation Shield (Remove and Replace)</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. TOP RECIRCULATION SHIELD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. RECIRCULATION MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the lower charge air cooler mounting bolts from the lower frame assembly (
                <hotlnk document="s12010_9.xml" xrefid="f1201051">Figure 51, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the recirculation shield mounting bolts along the front top of the
                radiator frame (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201017">Figure 17, Item 2</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the top radiator recirculation shield.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove upper radiator hose (
                <hotlnk document="s12010_5.xml" xrefid="f1201021">Figure 21, Item 1</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Refer to Section 1.4. COOLING SYSTEM RADIATOR HOSE REMOVAL, steps 1 and 2.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant, lift and rotate the charge air cooler up and out, away (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201018">Figure 18</hotlnk>) from the radiator. Passenger side charge air cooler
                discharge pipe must clear radiator frame before removal.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1201018" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201018.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Charge Air Cooler Removal Swing Out</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. RADIATOR CORE</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With passenger side charge air cooler discharge pipe clear of passenger side radiator frame
                and radiator core, move charge air cooler toward drivers side of chassis (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201019">Figure 19</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201019" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201019.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 19. Charge Air Cooler Removal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. CHARGE AIR COOLER</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DRIVERS SIDE SURGE TANK</callout1>
                <callout1>3. STAY ROD RADIATOR BRACKET</callout1>
                <callout1>4. RADIATOR SIDE FRAME</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With an assistant, lift and remove charge air cooler from chassis (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1201020">Figure 20</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place charge air cooler in a secure out of the way location.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1201020" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg12/G1201020.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 20. Lifting and Removing Charge Air Cooler</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. RADIATOR TOP FRAME</callout1>
                <callout1>2. DRIVERS SIDE SURGE TANK</callout1>
                <callout1>3. CAPPED CHARGE AIR COOLER PORT</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
